      <section eId="sec_CHC-1451">
        <num>CHC 1451</num>
        <heading>1451. Â Conversion to voluntary status</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1451__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>No director of a treatment facility shall prohibit any minor with mental illness or minor suffering from substance abuse from applying for conversion of involuntary or emergency admission status to voluntary admission status.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1451__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Any minor patient on an involuntary admission status shall have the right to apply for a writ of habeas corpus to have his admission status changed to voluntary status.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72947</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
